You'll rewrite this existing application's code to ES6 syntax. The application is used by parking lot attendants to monitor the number of cars currently parked. 

Here's your starter code. Take a good look at it. You have all the code you'll need except for a few lines we'll add here, Your main tasks are rewriting some of the code to ES6 syntax.

1. Add these two lines to the code. The code represents something called event listeners. They add functionality to the buttons by detecting a click and calling a function after this click occurs.

```JavaScript
buttonAdd.addEventListener("click", add);
buttonSubtract.addEventListener("click", subtract);

